# splat-lab (host-side mirror of `zip@jetson:~/splat-lab/`)

This folder mirrors what lives on the Jetson at `~/splat-lab/`. Edit here,
`scp` to the Jetson to deploy. Read `REPORT.md` first — it's the session
handoff and tells you what works, what's blocked, and what to do next.

## Quick links

- **`MISSION.md`** — agent brief / quality bar
- **`REPORT.md`** — current state, measured numbers, known issues, next-session
  plan (read this before doing anything)
- **`Dockerfile.splat`** — derived from `dustynv/l4t-pytorch:r36.4.0`, adds
  Depth Anything 3, gsplat 1.5.3, xformers + pycolmap stubs, torchvision
  backup/restore around the pip install. Builds to `splat-lab:latest` (~15.5 GB).
- **`launcher.sh`** — one-command end-to-end:
  `./launcher.sh <scan_id> [duration_s] [max_views]`
- **`live.html`** — the live RGB + DAv2 depth + YOLO + tegrastats dashboard.
  Deployed at `~/splat-lab/scenes/index.html` on the Jetson, served by nginx
  at `:8090/` (or `:8443/` HTTPS).
- **`requirements.txt`** — host-side Python deps (no torch — that's in the
  container)
- **`scripts/`** — every Python script the pipeline uses

## What does what

| Script | Where it runs | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `live_stream.py` | host venv (perception-lab .venv) | aiohttp daemon serving RGB+depth+detections+health on :8092. Persistent via systemd unit `splat-lab-live.service`. |
| `capture.py` | host venv | one-shot v4l2 capture + YOLO11n score-gate → keyframes + detections.jsonl |
| `bake.py` | `splat-lab:latest` container | DA3-SMALL inference + backproject → 3DGS PLY + settings.json. **Currently produces a valid PLY that doesn't render — see REPORT.md** |
| `annotate.py` | host venv | YOLO bboxes through DA3 extrinsics → world coords → SuperSplat hotspots in settings.json |
| `da3_canary.py` | container | DA3 load + depth canary + multi-view timing |
| `da3_infer.py` | container | Legacy DA3 wrapper kept for reference |
| `train_gsplat.py` | container | Reserved for the proper k-NN-init bake.py rework (REPORT.md → "next session") |
| `validate_ply.py` | anywhere | byte-level 3DGS PLY format validator |
| `ws_reload.py` | host venv | aiohttp WebSocket broadcaster for atomic-file-reload pings |
| `make_synthetic_ply.py` | anywhere | 5000-gaussian colored sphere (Day-1 smoke test) |
| `make_huge_test_ply.py` | anywhere | 9-corner debug cube at origin (proves viewer works) |
| `make_9_at_livedemo.py` | anywhere | 9-corner cube at livedemo bbox (camera-config sanity test) |
| `make_hybrid_ply.py` | anywhere | livedemo positions + uniform white opaque (renders as dark silhouette — proved coplanar issue) |
| `inspect_gs_output.py` | container | DA3 Prediction schema diagnostic |

## Deploy to the Jetson

```bash
# from this folder, sync to ~/splat-lab/ on the Jetson
rsync -av --delete --exclude=logs/ ./ zip-jetson:~/splat-lab/

# or just scp a single file you edited
scp scripts/bake.py zip-jetson:~/splat-lab/scripts/
```

## Open the live dashboard in your browser

The Jetson serves on `192.168.55.1:8090` (USB-C) and `:8443` (HTTPS). For
WebGPU you need a **secure context** — use an SSH tunnel to localhost:

```bash
# from VSCode / Claude Code: pick "jetson-splat" in the launch.json
# OR run manually:
ssh -L 8090:127.0.0.1:8090 -L 8443:127.0.0.1:8443 -N zip-jetson
# then open http://localhost:8090/ in any Chromium
```

## What is and isn't shipping

| | Status |
|---|---|
| Live RGB + YOLO + DAv2 depth + telemetry dashboard | ✅ ship-ready |
| nginx HTTPS + isolation triple (COOP/COEP/CORP) | ✅ ship-ready |
| DA3 inference container | ✅ ship-ready |
| SuperSplat Viewer (verified with test cubes) | ✅ ship-ready |
| Auto-annotation from YOLO11n | ✅ ship-ready (works on any viewable splat) |
| **DA3 → browser-viewable splat** | ❌ blocked on k-NN-init refactor (REPORT.md) |

## Related dirs

- `C:\zip\jetson\` — zip-brain repo (the robot's Python brain — separate
  concern; not part of splat-lab)
- `C:\zip\jetson-containers\` — dusty-nv jetson-containers clone (used to
  build `splat-lab:latest`)
- `C:\zip\.claude\launch.json` — has the `jetson-splat` ssh-tunnel entry
  that maps Windows `localhost:8090/8443` → Jetson, the only way Chrome
  treats the dashboard as a secure context (WebGPU + SAB)
